 have a different future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aPrisonerszUnited States. 0aPrisonszUnited StatesxOfficials and employees. 0aSolitary confinementzUnited States. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh  acarceral residents.  acorrectional staff.  ainterviews.  aprison reform.  aprisons.  aqualitative.  areentry.  arestricted housing units.  asolitary confinement.1 aHattery, Angela.1 aMagnuson, Shannon.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2022 Englishz978311099300408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2022z9783110993011oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076648640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363124340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503631243423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503631243/original  a978-3-11-076648-6  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099300-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2022  aZDB-23-DGGb2022